name: Viva Panjim

reviews.review_text:
One of the oldest authentic Goan-Portuguese cuisine. But we got a bit saucy in all.
I ordered orange honey pork steak, barbecue prawns, mixed seafood sizzler (yea,i made a mistake, all came with honey and sauce).

We got scammed this time, lol ðŸ˜†.

But Chicken chilly fry was yummy (it was dry).
And lime soda was good.

Best time to visit 7pm to 10pm.

A cozy restaurant inside a heritage home. The ambience is warm and vintage. Service is prompt. Food is definitely good. I tried the pork roast. Was delicious with tender pork cuts tossed in a sauce. The seafood is worth trying.

First of all let me state that we came an hour before closing time. I don't know how relevant this is but I'll mention it here.
We had 4 things and none of them met my expection. The chicken chilly fry was the only 'ok' one, the prawns barbeque was just about fine but the prawns themselves were good but they aredrowned in a sweet garlicky sauce( could have mentioned it somewhere on the menu, or maybe ask the waiter to mention it to the customer?), next up was the seafood sizzler, which to no suprise was also sweet!! The seafoody flavour just was not there and we had one among us who had their sizzler before and even she was surprised at how bad this was.
And finally the most disappointing one, the orange honey steak pork. It was drowned in the same sweet sauce as the prawns,( so just recycling the same sauce for every dish i guess??If i wanted something this sweet  I would've gone to an ice cream store. It was also on the firmer side, not what you usually expect from pork.
The waiter seemed cold, but then again they might've been rushing since it was near closing time.
To sum it up, had high expectations going by reviews and even suggestions from friends but had to leave feeling extremely disappointed!

description:
### Discovering the Culinary Charm of Viva Panjim

Nestled in the heart of Cavelossim, Goa, **Viva Panjim** has garnered a warm reputation with an impressive rating of **4.3** from **4,390 reviews**. A treasure for gastronomes, the restaurant is renowned for its authentic **Goan-Portuguese** cuisine, with signature dishes like **pork xacuti**, comforting **bebinca**, and decadent **caramel pudding** resounding in customer feedback. 

### Welcoming Ambiance

Walking into Viva Panjim, guests are immediately embraced by the cozy, vintage charm of a heritage home. The interior boasts warm tones and rustic dÃ©cor accented by traditional artifacts that transport diners back in time. The lighting is soft and inviting, creating an atmosphere perfect for intimate dinners or family gatherings. As one review notes, the vibe is conducive for visits between **7 PM and 10 PM**, drawing in a lively yet relaxed crowd. The photos further emphasize the delightful setting with immaculate table arrangements and a welcoming ambiance.

### A Culinary Journey Through Authenticity

The menu at Viva Panjim showcases a bounty of Goan flavors, and patrons praise the **pork roast**, characterized by tender cuts enveloped in rich sauce, exhibiting a blend of spices that define the region's culinary ethos. The **mixed seafood sizzler**, though a topic of mixed reviews, promises an enticing experience, while the **orange honey pork steak** is noted for its creative twist, despite some diners finding it overly sweet. Vegetarian options are available, catering to diverse dietary preferences.

Presentation is artfully done; each dish arrives looking as vibrantly appealing as it tastes. Customer photos reveal beautifully plated food, rich in color and texture, making the dining experience not just a meal, but a feast for the eyes.

### Service That Leaves an Impression

The service at Viva Panjim receives high marks for promptness and cordiality. Despite some feedback regarding the staff being a bit rushed during peak hours, it appears that most diners appreciate the friendly demeanor of the waitstaff. Guests have remarked on the attentive service that does its best to cater to specific requests, ensuring that the dining experience is enjoyable from start to finish.

### The Pulse of Popularity

Viva Panjim radiates with social media buzz, buoyed by countless positive reviews highlighting its authentic cuisine. Customers frequently remark on their high expectations being met, although there are a few mixed experiences with specific dishes. The restaurant has established itself as a go-to destination for both locals and tourists looking for a genuine taste of Goa. Its recognition is reflected not just in reviews, but through a loyal customer base that continues to sing its praises across various platforms.

### Visual Delights

The imagery associated with Viva Panjim paints a vivid picture of the restaurant's offerings and atmosphere. Photos reveal mouth-watering dishes, from the caramel pudding elegantly served to vibrant sizzlers that tantalize the taste buds. The warm, vintage interior is captured beautifully, showcasing the inviting essence of this heritage locale.

In conclusion, Viva Panjim stands as a exceptional culinary gem in Goa, promising an authentic experience that tantalizes the palate while providing a warm atmosphere. Whether you are indulging in the renowned **bebinca** or savoring the **pork xacuti**, this establishment invites you to relish every moment of your visit.
